Web proxy:

1. Make sure Lamp phpmyadmin and apache is running on LAMP

2. Make another Ubuntu ec2 this is for the WEB tier

3. ssh and port 80, both anywhere

4. sudo apt update, sudo apt upgrade

5. sudo apt install nginx

6. cd /etc/nginx/sites-available/

7. ls, should have default file

Making the reverse proxy:
8. sudo unlink /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default

9. sudo nano reverse-proxy.conf

type in: server {listen 80;location / {proxy_pass http://'';}}

'' = ip address of private lamp


10. ls /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

11. sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/reverse-proxy.conf /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/reverse-proxy.conf


12. ls /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
Shows symbolic link

13. sudo nano nginx.conf

14. sudo systemctl restart nginx

15. systemctl status nginx

16. take public ip of webtier ec2, post in browser

17. 
